pageContext.claim: “If we didn't have all these interest rates, you know, who thought he was going to raise interest rates but if we didn't have that we'd be at 5.2 [percent quarterly GDP growth] and the stock market would be up 10,000 points more.”
pageContext.analysis: There is no basis for Trump's claim that GDP growth and stock market gains would soar without higher interest rates. The Federal Reserve has raised rates to prevent the economy from overheating and falling into recession.
